1
00:00:13,708 --> 00:00:15,333
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:20,083
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:23,833
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:26,042 --> 00:00:27,958
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:30,208 --> 00:00:32,042
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:36,893
(Jirol / Kim Nam-soo, Mr. Kim / Song Won-soo, Chairman Lee /
Choi Sang-hak) (Officer Sin / Im Chang-seop, Mina / Heo Ye-seul)

7
00:00:36,917 --> 00:00:41,333
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 3)

8
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:44,333
(The Secret of Wooju Bakery)

9
00:01:09,667 --> 00:01:10,667
Are you crazy?

10
00:01:38,292 --> 00:01:41,917
(Wooju Bakery)

11
00:01:46,583 --> 00:01:48,042
What are you guys doing?

12
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:50,143
Looks like they're fixing a broken engine.

13
00:01:50,167 --> 00:01:51,292
What are you talking about?

14
00:01:51,417 --> 00:01:54,083
Our spaceship runs on plasma energy.

15
00:01:54,208 --> 00:01:56,208
The balance is off. We
need sound waves to fix it.

16
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Hachi!

17
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:06,458
How did they get here?

18
00:02:06,583 --> 00:02:07,708
Huh?

19
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:12,125
Hachi!

20
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:13,250
Found it.

21
00:02:13,625 --> 00:02:15,042
What's going on? What happened?

22
00:02:16,542 --> 00:02:17,750
Finally!

23
00:02:22,458 --> 00:02:24,208
I can use this to fix the machine.

24
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:54,875
Not bad.

25
00:02:55,792 --> 00:02:59,875
But how do you knead
the dough without a recipe?

26
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,250
I told you, I have taste buds in my hands.

27
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:04,476
They're five times more
sensitive than your tongues.

28
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,292
So I don't even need to taste-test.

29
00:03:08,042 --> 00:03:09,250
That's impressive.

30
00:03:17,125 --> 00:03:19,625
That's why I don't want to share my secret.

31
00:03:22,042 --> 00:03:23,722
But if you really want it, I can tell you.

32
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:27,542
Don't expect a free lesson.

33
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:30,458
If you give me the recipe,

34
00:03:31,417 --> 00:03:33,167
I'll cut the final payment in half.

35
00:03:33,292 --> 00:03:34,500
Six months!

36
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,875
Back off a little.

37
00:04:28,333 --> 00:04:29,458
Chairman.

38
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:33,083
Please look at this.

39
00:04:34,583 --> 00:04:35,583
What is this?

40
00:04:35,667 --> 00:04:37,333
It seems there's trouble at Wooju Bakery.

41
00:04:37,458 --> 00:04:38,917
Let's go, now.

42
00:04:39,375 --> 00:04:40,542
Yes, understood.

43
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:45,208
It's really true, ahjussi!

44
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:49,792
- I told you, I'm not an old man.
- Whatever, I'm not lying.

45
00:04:50,167 --> 00:04:50,917
Chief Choi.

46
00:04:51,042 --> 00:04:52,167
I'm back.

47
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:56,667
Wait over there.

48
00:04:59,875 --> 00:05:02,458
See if there are any
aliens that look like that.

49
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:05,250
Wait, this one looks a bit like it.

50
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:07,125
It's actually cute.

51
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:08,667
Oh my.

52
00:05:08,792 --> 00:05:12,583
Senior, I think we really need
to investigate this properly.

53
00:05:12,708 --> 00:05:15,958
If you start spouting that nonsense
about aliens and UFOs again...

54
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:17,917
Get out of here, you're
giving me a headache.

55
00:05:18,042 --> 00:05:21,917
No, I'm serious. I don't
think that lady is lying.

56
00:05:22,042 --> 00:05:24,958
Enough. We have a
pile of cases to deal with.

57
00:05:25,083 --> 00:05:27,500
Go check out that recycling
center the woman mentioned.

58
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:31,708
Chief Choi.

59
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:32,875
Yes?

60
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,250
Who's that person you brought with you?

61
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:38,500
He doesn't seem to have anywhere to go.

62
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:40,375
So I brought him to the station for now.

63
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,292
I've got plenty of space, okay?

64
00:05:42,583 --> 00:05:44,833
I came here because I wanted to.

65
00:05:44,958 --> 00:05:46,250
That's why I'm here.

66
00:05:48,208 --> 00:05:50,583
Is the police station your
personal playground?

67
00:05:51,208 --> 00:05:52,768
If you can play in it,
isn't it a playground?

68
00:05:52,792 --> 00:05:54,375
What's the difference?

69
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,000
- Hey everyone!
- Be serious.

70
00:05:56,125 --> 00:05:57,643
My friend is at the
police station right now.

71
00:05:57,667 --> 00:05:59,167
Say hi to everyone.

72
00:06:02,250 --> 00:06:03,583
I'm curious.

73
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:07,375
What did that ugly woman do?

74
00:06:08,083 --> 00:06:09,625
What did you just say?

75
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:12,250
You're the ugly one, how
dare you talk about others.

76
00:06:12,375 --> 00:06:12,833
Unbelievable.

77
00:06:12,958 --> 00:06:16,292
Everyone, this ugly person
here for questioning...

78
00:06:16,417 --> 00:06:17,684
Actually dared to talk back to me.

79
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:20,042
Wait, someone said he's handsome?

80
00:06:20,292 --> 00:06:21,583
For real?

81
00:06:21,875 --> 00:06:22,875
Where is he handsome?

82
00:06:22,979 --> 00:06:24,771
I'm not handsome, I'm pretty!

83
00:06:24,917 --> 00:06:25,378
Oh my god.

84
00:06:25,402 --> 00:06:26,809
I'm pretty, okay? And who
gave you permission to film?

85
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:27,708
Officer Shin.

86
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:28,667
Yeah?

87
00:06:28,792 --> 00:06:30,393
Should we head to the recycling center first?

88
00:06:30,417 --> 00:06:33,042
Why are you taking my stuff? Give it back!

89
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:34,583
Ugh, seriously!

90
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,458
Let it go!

91
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:37,083
So annoying.

92
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:39,250
Wait! I'm coming too.

93
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:49,042
It's the Chairman.

94
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:49,625
Hmm.

95
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:51,750
What is that guy doing here?

96
00:06:51,875 --> 00:06:53,125
Who knows?

97
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:58,250
Well, well, long time no see.

98
00:06:58,375 --> 00:06:59,684
We live in the same neighborhood,

99
00:06:59,708 --> 00:07:02,292
yet it's so hard to run into each other.

100
00:07:02,417 --> 00:07:03,542
Isn't it?

101
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:06,750
Didn't we agree to pretend
we don't know each other?

102
00:07:06,875 --> 00:07:07,708
Yeah.

103
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:10,417
Since you both said
you'd leave Earth quietly,

104
00:07:10,542 --> 00:07:12,833
I promised I wouldn't
interfere with your plans.

105
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:15,768
You said you were
going to fix the spaceship,

106
00:07:15,792 --> 00:07:17,268
and I even set up a workshop for you.

107
00:07:17,292 --> 00:07:21,167
Why did you steal all the
spaceships that landed on Earth?

108
00:07:21,292 --> 00:07:22,875
This isn't a workshop.

109
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:23,875
It's a construction site!

110
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,250
Give us back our spaceship!

111
00:07:30,958 --> 00:07:33,208
That's not the deal we made.

112
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:37,000
Just fix the Wooju Bakery building.

113
00:07:37,125 --> 00:07:40,375
Then I'll return the ship
and give you the parts.

114
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:41,580
You didn't forget, did you?

115
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:43,667
That Wooju Bakery building...

116
00:07:43,792 --> 00:07:45,792
It's not just some ordinary machine.

117
00:07:45,917 --> 00:07:47,517
You should know that better than anyone.

118
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:49,417
It's a living organism.

119
00:07:49,542 --> 00:07:50,542
A living organism!

120
00:07:50,583 --> 00:07:53,125
You can't just patch it up.

121
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:54,375
It needs proper treatment.

122
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:56,625
Then go! Go treat it!

123
00:07:56,750 --> 00:08:01,518
But then why did you kidnap...
the guy who was trying to ruin the bakery?

124
00:08:01,542 --> 00:08:02,750
That...

125
00:08:03,083 --> 00:08:04,708
Do you have proof that we did it?

126
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:06,643
I checked all the security
cameras in the area.

127
00:08:06,667 --> 00:08:07,726
You kidnapped someone
at the Chinese restaurant,

128
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:10,792
and dragged them all the
way here. It's all on tape.

129
00:08:10,917 --> 00:08:12,250
Take these two away.

130
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:13,875
No, no!

131
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,480
I really didn't know that YouTuber
was one of yours! Really...

132
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:17,333
I told you to stop acting.

133
00:08:17,458 --> 00:08:19,938
- I really didn't know, okay?
- You should've said that sooner.

134
00:08:20,042 --> 00:08:21,208
I can't go, I can't!

135
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,958
I'm all bruised up!

136
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:25,708
- I can't, I can't!
- What do we do...

137
00:08:33,042 --> 00:08:35,125
Bro, the staff here are so handsome.

138
00:08:38,292 --> 00:08:39,772
I can't even capture their movements.

139
00:08:50,083 --> 00:08:51,917
- Oh~
- Oh~

140
00:08:59,167 --> 00:09:01,833
Why are there so many
people all of a sudden?

141
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:06,042
Isn't it good? We're making a lot of money.

142
00:09:06,167 --> 00:09:07,559
What are you complaining about, boss?

143
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,667
This isn't the bakery I dreamed of.

144
00:09:11,292 --> 00:09:13,125
Then what does your dream bakery look like?

145
00:09:13,785 --> 00:09:16,208
It's not about having no
customers or not making money.

146
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:19,208
It's a place where
people can come to relax,

147
00:09:20,250 --> 00:09:21,458
release some stress,

148
00:09:21,583 --> 00:09:23,500
and feel healed.

149
00:09:24,583 --> 00:09:26,417
That's the kind of bakery I want to run.

150
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:29,351
Why are you looking at me like that?

151
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:31,792
Don't you ever look at the customers?

152
00:09:33,625 --> 00:09:35,208
Don't they all look happy?

153
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:44,333
The only unhappy person here is you.

154
00:09:47,375 --> 00:09:50,003
Scream, everybody, dance!

155
00:09:50,167 --> 00:09:52,417
Hi. Alright.

156
00:09:53,159 --> 00:09:54,659
Thank you.

157
00:09:54,792 --> 00:09:55,792
What's up man?

158
00:10:20,042 --> 00:10:21,833
You must be Prince Raon, right?

159
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:24,417
I'm here to ask for your help.

160
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:25,708
What's wrong?

161
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:28,917
Two of our companions have been kidnapped.

162
00:10:29,083 --> 00:10:29,750
By whom?

163
00:10:29,875 --> 00:10:31,583
They're alien criminals.

164
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:35,000
They're wanted across the galaxy.
They're extremely dangerous.

165
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:38,917
Ma'am, I don't know what your
relationship is with that human,

166
00:10:39,042 --> 00:10:44,458
but you should report this
to the police, not come here.

167
00:10:44,583 --> 00:10:46,417
It's not just us who are in danger.

168
00:10:46,542 --> 00:10:49,708
Those people are targeting the bakery.

169
00:10:50,583 --> 00:10:55,625
Targeting our bakery? Why?

170
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:57,292
I'm telling the truth.

171
00:11:01,708 --> 00:11:05,348
"Today's Revenue: ₩13,060,800
Monthly Revenue: Approx. ₩41,818,600"

172
00:11:05,958 --> 00:11:07,208
Raon.

173
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:10,458
It seems word has gotten out
that we're making a lot of money!

174
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:11,625
My phone...

175
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:14,458
I need to call my brother!

176
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:25,583
Brother! Something big happened!

177
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:27,542
Some criminals are targeting our bakery.

178
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:29,559
It seems the news about our
bakery going viral has spread.

179
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:32,458
Really? Targeting a bakery?

180
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:35,125
- Yes...
- Who said that?

181
00:11:35,542 --> 00:11:38,000
Rap? What did he do with rap?

182
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:39,875
There are a lot of scammers out there.

183
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,708
They're just trying to
scare people to get money.

184
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:44,875
Don't worry, just stay put.

185
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,708
I'll head to the bakery later.

186
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:49,083
I'm busy right now, we'll talk later.

187
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:52,792
Who was that?

188
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:55,833
Um... my brother.

189
00:11:55,958 --> 00:11:59,500
Don't answer the phone
like that for anyone else.

190
00:12:00,292 --> 00:12:02,375
Answering with that
handsome, gentle voice...

191
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,292
it'll make people fall in love with you.

192
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,333
I'm your number one fan, you know.

193
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:22,083
You've changed. You would've
rushed over here before.

194
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:30,958
So, they admitted it right here?

195
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:33,625
That they're aliens? Is that what you mean?

196
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:34,500
Exactly.

197
00:12:34,625 --> 00:12:35,708
Officer Shin.

198
00:12:36,167 --> 00:12:38,000
That's enough. Let's go back.

199
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:40,083
Wait, what do you mean 'that's enough'?

200
00:12:40,208 --> 00:12:42,208
Are you saying I staged this?

201
00:12:42,333 --> 00:12:43,417
Are you questioning me?

202
00:12:43,542 --> 00:12:45,167
I didn't say you staged it.

203
00:12:45,292 --> 00:12:48,500
No, the look on your face... it
clearly said I was lying for views.

204
00:12:48,625 --> 00:12:50,125
You definitely had that look.

205
00:12:50,250 --> 00:12:52,226
Are you looking down on
me because I'm a YouTuber?

206
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:53,667
Who's looking down on you?

207
00:12:53,792 --> 00:12:57,542
The point is to figure out what
the aliens are doing on Earth.

208
00:12:57,667 --> 00:12:59,083
Isn't that the police's job?

209
00:12:59,208 --> 00:13:02,542
No, it's not just one or two aliens.

210
00:13:02,667 --> 00:13:04,601
A whole group of them
came to Earth to cause trouble.

211
00:13:04,625 --> 00:13:05,375
Does that even make sense?

212
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,500
Senior.

213
00:13:08,042 --> 00:13:10,000
I think she has a point.

214
00:13:10,125 --> 00:13:10,667
What?

215
00:13:10,792 --> 00:13:14,375
Whatever conspiracy these
aliens are plotting on Earth,

216
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,417
it should be up to us
police to investigate.

217
00:13:16,542 --> 00:13:17,934
We need to get to the bottom of this.

218
00:13:17,958 --> 00:13:18,792
Hey!

219
00:13:18,917 --> 00:13:20,997
Do you think the police are
the Earth Defense Force?

220
00:13:21,292 --> 00:13:24,750
Police are here to protect
the people, you get it?

221
00:13:24,875 --> 00:13:27,500
Um, our conversation just now,

222
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:29,250
I recorded the whole thing.

223
00:13:29,375 --> 00:13:32,292
Once I upload this to
YouTube, you guys are finished.

224
00:13:34,042 --> 00:13:35,125
Ugh, so annoying.

225
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:37,708
Woo-hyuk, come here for a second.

226
00:13:37,833 --> 00:13:38,417
Huh?

227
00:13:38,542 --> 00:13:39,875
I said come here.

228
00:13:48,917 --> 00:13:50,375
What are you doing?

229
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:54,500
Delete all the videos.

230
00:13:55,542 --> 00:13:56,792
Delete them now.

231
00:13:56,917 --> 00:14:00,250
Now, can you be my Seoul tour guide?

232
00:14:00,375 --> 00:14:04,875
But are those two really going to be okay?

233
00:14:05,458 --> 00:14:06,458
Of course they are.

234
00:14:06,583 --> 00:14:09,917
I've already wiped that
conversation from their memories.

235
00:14:10,042 --> 00:14:12,333
Hey, you two over there.

236
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:14,583
Yes, you.

237
00:14:14,708 --> 00:14:15,792
It's the police station.

238
00:14:15,917 --> 00:14:18,292
Just head back to the station.

239
00:14:18,417 --> 00:14:20,042
Alright, get up, get up.

240
00:14:20,792 --> 00:14:22,250
Yes, understood.

241
00:14:22,375 --> 00:14:23,208
Alright, take care.

242
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:24,583
Officer Shin.

243
00:14:24,708 --> 00:14:25,542
Officer Shin.

244
00:14:25,667 --> 00:14:27,542
Don't come back.

245
00:14:31,375 --> 00:14:32,208
Handled?

246
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:33,833
Everything is handled.

247
00:14:34,917 --> 00:14:36,167
So you mean...

248
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:40,042
that the Chairman has been staying on Earth

249
00:14:40,583 --> 00:14:41,625
because of this bakery?

250
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,167
I told you so.

251
00:14:43,292 --> 00:14:47,083
Could there be some
secret to this building?

252
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:50,542
Actually, this place is a
massive mechanical device.

253
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:54,167
It can generate enough
energy to destroy the Earth.

254
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:58,917
This place is not just a
building, I can feel it.

255
00:14:59,042 --> 00:15:01,833
Yes, it's a living organism.

256
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:06,500
Are you saying this building is alive?

257
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:11,000
Did our ship crashing

258
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:15,510
have something to do
with this building too?

259
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,625
What on earth is this?

260
00:15:23,375 --> 00:15:24,833
A harvester machine.

261
00:15:27,875 --> 00:15:28,958
Underneath Wooju Bakery,

262
00:15:29,083 --> 00:15:32,625
there's a device connected that
drains the Earth's vast life energy.

263
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:34,958
The Chairman planned
to sell that energy secretly

264
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:36,625
and make a fortune.

265
00:15:39,542 --> 00:15:41,262
Luckily, it stopped operating 15 years ago.

266
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:43,417
But if it starts up again,

267
00:15:43,542 --> 00:15:46,208
all of Earth will be in danger.

268
00:15:47,125 --> 00:15:48,250
I like ittt!

269
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,917
Um, Your Highness... no, wait.

270
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:57,250
What should I call you?

271
00:15:57,375 --> 00:15:58,792
My name is Q.

272
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:03,792
But... why aren't you going
home? Why are you still here?

273
00:16:03,917 --> 00:16:05,458
Didn't I just say?

274
00:16:05,583 --> 00:16:09,375
I don't know anyone here,
and I have nowhere to go.

275
00:16:11,083 --> 00:16:12,958
So what are you going to do now?

276
00:16:16,417 --> 00:16:18,375
Do you want to be my tour guide?

277
00:16:20,042 --> 00:16:24,000
I'm a police officer, not a tour guide.

278
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:25,792
Senior, look at this.

279
00:16:25,917 --> 00:16:27,708
We've already received several reports.

280
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:32,333
They all say a UFO landed
in our area this afternoon.

281
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:33,958
What did the Chief say?

282
00:16:34,083 --> 00:16:35,417
He told us to ignore it.

283
00:16:36,125 --> 00:16:37,375
Just do as the Chief says.

284
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,250
I just feel like something is off.

285
00:16:39,375 --> 00:16:41,292
Like the fire at Wooju
Bakery the other day.

286
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:43,625
I think aliens really have
come to our neighborhood.

287
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:46,417
Didn't I tell you to stop
reading so many sci-fi comics?

288
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,708
Senior!

289
00:16:49,125 --> 00:16:52,458
NASA is investigating
the alien situation too.

290
00:16:52,583 --> 00:16:56,000
Even though many people
think it's just a conspiracy theory,

291
00:16:56,125 --> 00:16:59,542
I heard they come to Earth often

292
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:01,542
to abduct humans for experiments.

293
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,708
Aliens...

294
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:06,958
are they going to abduct Earthlings?

295
00:17:07,083 --> 00:17:08,833
Ah...

296
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,917
Well, I guess...

297
00:17:11,042 --> 00:17:14,583
there are some Earthlings who
are worth abducting, I suppose.

298
00:17:15,292 --> 00:17:16,625
But...

299
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:19,292
Why is this person here?

300
00:17:19,792 --> 00:17:21,917
It's a bit complicated.

301
00:17:22,042 --> 00:17:24,226
He's from abroad and doesn't
seem to have anywhere to go.

302
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:27,042
Which country? His Korean is so good.

303
00:17:27,750 --> 00:17:28,417
Um...

304
00:17:28,542 --> 00:17:30,542
It's Thailand, right?

305
00:17:31,292 --> 00:17:32,333
No.

306
00:17:32,458 --> 00:17:38,083
I come from a distant planet without love.

307
00:17:38,208 --> 00:17:40,458
I'm a traveler,

308
00:17:40,583 --> 00:17:42,500
searching for love.

309
00:17:54,583 --> 00:17:56,125
Why are you looking at me like that?

310
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:57,250
Nothing.

311
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,000
That was a bit dramatic.

312
00:18:06,083 --> 00:18:07,708
This place looks like a new nightclub.

313
00:18:07,833 --> 00:18:09,101
Looks like a popular spot to take photos.

314
00:18:09,125 --> 00:18:11,500
I heard it's the weirdest
bakery in the world.

315
00:18:11,625 --> 00:18:15,000
Like a bakery thrown together by aliens?

316
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,833
Officer Shin,

317
00:18:17,292 --> 00:18:20,500
he doesn't seem to have a
place to stay. What should we do?

318
00:18:20,625 --> 00:18:23,708
I've decided.

319
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:28,833
I'll stay at the police
officer's place tonight.

320
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:30,208
Huh?

321
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:33,625
Not at my place.

322
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:34,792
Yes, you can.

323
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:36,643
Calling in a complaint,

324
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:39,083
27-50 Wangri-dong, noise
complaint at the bakery.

325
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:41,288
Patrol cars in the area,
please respond immediately.

326
00:18:45,417 --> 00:18:46,250
On our way.

327
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,250
Your voice is truly charming.

328
00:18:48,375 --> 00:18:49,917
I like it.

329
00:18:53,917 --> 00:18:56,542
Earth is more romantic than I thought.

330
00:19:00,542 --> 00:19:04,500
Why are you waking up
the whole neighborhood?

331
00:19:04,625 --> 00:19:06,750
I'm very sorry.

332
00:19:09,250 --> 00:19:10,833
Police is here.

333
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:13,083
It's so noisy here, it's driving us crazy.

334
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:14,667
Can you do something about it?

335
00:19:17,083 --> 00:19:18,500
The kids can't even sleep.

336
00:19:18,625 --> 00:19:19,167
I'm very sorry.

337
00:19:19,292 --> 00:19:21,268
(Wooju Bakery) I thought a bakery
would be quiet. What is going on here?

338
00:19:21,292 --> 00:19:22,417
I'm sorry.

339
00:19:33,167 --> 00:19:36,958
Could that be an alien memory eraser?

340
00:19:37,083 --> 00:19:40,208
No, it's more like a
dissatisfaction eraser.

341
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:45,083
Alright, everyone go home
now. Stop crowding around.

342
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:49,125
Boss, what were those people doing outside?

343
00:19:49,250 --> 00:19:50,250
I don't know.

344
00:19:50,375 --> 00:19:52,875
They were making such a
scene just a moment ago,

345
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,917
and then they all just left.

346
00:19:55,042 --> 00:19:57,402
Your fiancé was shooting some
weird thing around out there.

347
00:20:00,208 --> 00:20:01,208
Q.

348
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:03,208
Are you using an emotion-regulating gun?

349
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:05,417
Huh? What's the problem?

350
00:20:05,542 --> 00:20:07,833
Isn't that for erasing memories?

351
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:11,500
You're one to talk, you
snuck onto Earth yourself.

352
00:20:13,542 --> 00:20:15,625
Wooju, are you okay?

353
00:20:16,542 --> 00:20:17,417
I'm fine.

354
00:20:17,542 --> 00:20:21,292
But the way they were
acting earlier was pretty scary.

355
00:20:21,417 --> 00:20:23,000
Sorry, Wooju. That just now...

356
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:25,042
Don't contact Woo-hyuk anymore.

357
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:26,625
Just come to me directly.

358
00:20:27,458 --> 00:20:30,958
I'll use that gun to take
care of everything for you.

359
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:35,917
I'll be borrowing Woo-hyuk now.

360
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:38,000
No!

361
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:47,226
This isn't the way I want things to be.

362
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:48,750
I said no!

363
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:51,708
Boss.

364
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:52,917
What?

365
00:20:53,042 --> 00:20:55,167
We earned a lot today.

366
00:20:55,292 --> 00:20:56,625
Do you know how much we made?

367
00:21:05,083 --> 00:21:05,833
What is this?

368
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:07,542
I didn't even do anything.

369
00:21:07,667 --> 00:21:08,958
You...

370
00:21:10,667 --> 00:21:11,667
(Closed)

371
00:21:13,167 --> 00:21:14,833
Good work, everyone.

372
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:18,500
Does anyone know where Q is staying?

373
00:21:24,917 --> 00:21:26,292
Can't he just sleep here?

374
00:21:28,917 --> 00:21:32,458
I'm not sleeping in this filthy place.

375
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:35,333
You take him. It would be good.

376
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:37,750
He can stay at my place tonight.

377
00:21:37,875 --> 00:21:39,875
Bro, don't you only have one room?

378
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,458
It's fine, I'll just sleep on the sofa.

379
00:21:42,583 --> 00:21:45,542
I'm heading out. Good work, everyone.

380
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:46,958
You...!

381
00:22:02,292 --> 00:22:04,417
Don't stay over there,
come lie down next to me.

382
00:22:04,708 --> 00:22:07,250
No... no thanks, I'm fine like this.

383
00:22:07,375 --> 00:22:09,917
I'm the type of person
who, if I want something,

384
00:22:10,042 --> 00:22:14,000
I'll chase it to the ends of
the universe until I get it.

385
00:22:17,458 --> 00:22:19,018
I really envy that confidence of yours.

386
00:22:19,125 --> 00:22:19,833
Why?

387
00:22:19,958 --> 00:22:23,208
Because I've never
gotten anything I wanted.

388
00:22:24,542 --> 00:22:26,208
That's perfect then.

389
00:22:26,333 --> 00:22:27,125
What do you mean?

390
00:22:27,250 --> 00:22:30,458
You'll soon have something you want.

391
00:22:30,583 --> 00:22:33,833
And it's the kind you won't
have to give up to anyone else.

392
00:22:42,208 --> 00:22:45,750
Is that toy gun really that dangerous?

393
00:22:45,875 --> 00:22:50,333
Yeah, it can control emotions,

394
00:22:50,458 --> 00:22:52,250
and it can also wipe memories.

395
00:22:53,958 --> 00:22:56,125
But it doesn't wipe everything clean.

396
00:22:58,208 --> 00:23:00,958
Huh? Wiping memories? Here we go again.

397
00:23:02,708 --> 00:23:04,417
We'll talk about it later.

398
00:23:04,542 --> 00:23:05,750
I'm going to take a shower.

399
00:23:05,850 --> 00:23:08,917
A shower? What's that?

400
00:23:09,042 --> 00:23:13,000
Wait, don't tell me... you've
never even taken a shower?

401
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:16,833
When my body gets
dirty, of course I wash it.

402
00:23:16,958 --> 00:23:19,333
But don't you use expensive
water to wash here?

403
00:23:19,875 --> 00:23:21,292
Then what else would you use?

404
00:23:21,958 --> 00:23:23,208
Air.

405
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:25,292
Wow! That's so gross.

406
00:23:25,750 --> 00:23:28,292
Doesn't that mean you're
not really washing at all?

407
00:23:28,417 --> 00:23:30,042
Move, I'm going to shower.

408
00:23:32,208 --> 00:23:34,125
Can I watch you shower?

409
00:23:35,667 --> 00:23:39,417
What the hell are you
talking about? Are you crazy?

410
00:23:40,583 --> 00:23:43,917
Because I've never seen
anyone shower with water.

411
00:23:51,458 --> 00:23:53,458
Didn't you say you'd never tried it?

412
00:24:07,583 --> 00:24:10,458
You're actually using water. How amazing.

413
00:24:10,583 --> 00:24:15,583
Don't get the wrong idea, I brought
you here so you could wash up too.

414
00:24:15,708 --> 00:24:17,028
Do I have to wash with water too?

415
00:24:20,375 --> 00:24:23,250
Hold on, wait until I'm
done before you start.

416
00:24:25,708 --> 00:24:27,917
Can you soap up my back for me?

417
00:24:28,042 --> 00:24:29,625
Soap?

418
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:32,000
Just like that, rub it on my back.

419
00:24:32,750 --> 00:24:33,792
Hurry up!

420
00:24:33,917 --> 00:24:35,542
How am I supposed to do it?

421
00:24:35,667 --> 00:24:37,458
Just rub it on!

422
00:24:40,375 --> 00:24:45,208
You have the soap, right? Use that.

423
00:25:01,292 --> 00:25:02,583
Come on.

424
00:25:02,708 --> 00:25:04,167
Hey! Get a move on!
